### S2-6 — Shared Redis Pub/Sub for SSE (Fan-out)

**Why:** Current: 1 Redis pubsub client per SSE connection. At 10k users = 10k Redis connections → OOM.

**[NEW] `apps/api/app/core/pubsub.py`**
```python
class PlanEventBus:
    """Single Redis subscriber per process; fan-out to per-user asyncio queues."""
    async def subscribe(self, user_id: str) -> asyncio.Queue: ...
    async def unsubscribe(self, user_id: str, q: asyncio.Queue): ...
    async def _run(self): ...  # background loop listening on Redis
```

**[MODIFY] `apps/api/app/main.py`**
- Start `PlanEventBus._run()` as a FastAPI lifespan background task.

**[MODIFY] `apps/api/app/api/v1/billing/routes/events.py`**
- Replace per-connection `redis_pool.pubsub()` with `await bus.subscribe(user_id)`.

**Result:** N SSE connections share 1 Redis subscriber per API process.

